snippet.textDisplay:
went to Costo on this weekend and was very unamused by there actions to stop the virus. Cart cleaning consisted of a guy spraying down the top of the handle, did not whip anything. So as long as the virus is only on the top part of those handles we should be safe, just don't grab the handle and touch the bottom side of them, or grab your cart by the side of them.
Came to check-out and it got worse. 3 Costco people per lane, Cashier, Person unloading carts and person loading cart (no bagging/boxing being done "to speed things along". The person in charge of putting the items in the cart would run around and spray down the protective glass panel between the cashier and the customer each time but that was it.

When it was my turn I stopped the guy from touching my cart and items, explained I would do it as I wanted to limit the people handling them. He got upset, so I then pointed out that he as nice as it was to see him wearing gloves, he didn't clean them between customers, meaning some he uncarted 30minutes ago could have had it and he was now passing it onto everyone that he uncarted since then. He got more upset at me for that. Since the store was busy even though they were limiting customers, it only took an hour standing in line to get inside. There was no dis-infecting the belts between customers either. Not much I could do about that. The girl loading carts didn't seem to care that I didn't want her loading my cart for me. During this process, they made sure to keep all customers away from staff and each other, which is great, but the three of them were all over each other, and all lanes seem to be the same way.
So when I got home I did try my best to follow the online tutorial on making everything safe, took items out of boxes/bags, cleaned everything down, left fruit and veg in a safe area for 2 days, changed clothes, then washed up.

snippet.textDisplay:
STORY TIME for anyone interested to know what it's like to be an essential employee in this Covid-19 pandemic.

I work at Walmart! At the start of the pandemic people were mostly thankful that we were open and still serving them💓. But as the days have passed I have seen people becoming more and more aggressive and extremely rude towards the employees of my store. Its heartbreaking truly, I am the only one in my family who is still going out in the quartine as I am supposedly "essential". It feels almost criminal🤫 steeping outside when there's literally no one on the streets walking👀. My parents dont want me out of my apartment🏙 rn but I still show up at work, coz we( walmart) are severely understaffed as a lot employees self isolated/ quartined ( I don't blame them, everyone wants to stay safe with their families 👨‍👩‍👧‍👦) but becoz of this we are under a lot of pressure to schedule people properly, hoping that they are ok and will show up. I understand that as a manager I am suppose to show up and serve our community. But what make things worse is that the customers treat us like shit💩, they have even abused🤬 some of my co-workers when they were asked to keep social distance. It's truly heartbreaking💔, our community should stand together in this critical time supporting and respecting one another instead of trying to humiliate and put false allegations (you guys are probably storing all the toilet paper🧻 and sanitizer for yourself) on us. Are you even sanitizing the counters? Yes Karen I am and I have been since the start of my shift like 10000 times. There are many many more ignorant bobbleheads that like to shop around for an hour to get a kitkat. Like seriously?🤦‍♀️ Look around yourselves people we ARE in the middle of a pandemic only step out if you need essential supplies. We are only allowed to shop during our breaks and we are NOT allowed to hide stuff from our customers. The employees working at any store are also human and love their lives very much so guess what after processing your order I am sanitizing my entire soul with that damn sanitizer🥺

(Side note - I am thankful for this job as I know a lot of my friends and family have lost theirs.) And also If you see an old man been able to get 2 sanitizers and you were allowed to get only one please understand that he probably took a taxi in the snow ( I am in Canada) Please dont make a scene out of it and try to understand the situation. If there was no limit the person ahead of you must have taken it all. All I am asking is for a little bit of humanity for the rest of the world🌎! We are in this together!!🙏🏻
